name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $url
desc: Returns: An absolute URI that is used to identify this graph definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this graph definition is (or will be) published. The URL SHOULD include the major version of the graph definition. For more information see [Technical and Business Versions](resource.html#versions).

name: $::version
desc: Returns: The identifier that is used to identify this version of the graph definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the graph definition author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it might be a timestamp (e.g. yyyymmdd) if a managed version is not available. There is also no expectation that versions can be placed in a lexicographical sequence.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The identifier that is used to identify this version of the graph definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the graph definition author and is not expected to be globally unique.

name: $::name
desc: Returns: A natural language name identifying the graph definition. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation.

pvardefs.name: pValue

name: $experimental
